Title: Logic and Computation
Body: Date: Wed, 20 Nov 1996 19:10:24 GMT Server: Apache/1.1.1 Content-type: text/html Content-length: 2093 Last-modified: Fri, 25 Oct 1996 19:44:27 GMT Logic and Computation Logic and Computation (formerly the Institute for Advanced Concepts in Programming Language Theory ) The focus of this research group is on logic in computer science, with particular interest in lambda calculus and functional programming, types, constructive mathematics, proof theory, linear logic, and semantics.
